<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1782,2023]" pageId="2" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis box="[199,364,1782,1807]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="586">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Pygofer dorsal appendage slender, with many microspines apically (
<figureCitation box="[1160,1231,1782,1807]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1690,1713]" captionTargetBox="[165,1417,193,1648]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1424,193,1669]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Arboridia cincta Song &amp; Li, sp. nov.: 1, Abdominal apodemes; 2, Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 3, Subgenital plate; 4, Style; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238916/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="586">
Fig. 
<number box="[1214,1231,1783,1807]" pageId="2" pageNumber="586" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate with basolateral angulate projection prominent, with 
<number box="[741,755,1819,1843]" pageId="2" pageNumber="586" value="3.0">3</number>
macrosetae on lateral surface and numerous short stout setae from subbase to apex; apical 
<number box="[483,494,1855,1879]" pageId="2" pageNumber="586" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[506,521,1855,1879]" pageId="2" pageNumber="586" value="3.0">3</number>
, with dark color (
<figureCitation box="[724,793,1854,1879]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1690,1713]" captionTargetBox="[165,1417,193,1648]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1424,193,1669]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Arboridia cincta Song &amp; Li, sp. nov.: 1, Abdominal apodemes; 2, Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 3, Subgenital plate; 4, Style; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238916/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="586">
Fig. 
<number box="[777,793,1855,1879]" pageId="2" pageNumber="586" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Style apex with 
<number box="[999,1013,1855,1879]" pageId="2" pageNumber="586" value="3.0">3</number>
short toothlike points; preapical lobe well developed (
<figureCitation box="[349,425,1890,1915]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1690,1713]" captionTargetBox="[165,1417,193,1648]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1424,193,1669]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Arboridia cincta Song &amp; Li, sp. nov.: 1, Abdominal apodemes; 2, Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 3, Subgenital plate; 4, Style; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238916/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="586">
Fig. 
<number box="[408,425,1891,1915]" pageId="2" pageNumber="586" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with pair of long slender subapical processes bowed laterad and curved ventrobasally; gonopore long, apical on ventral surface; preatrium slender, bent at right angle in lateral view, much longer than dorsal apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[476,577,1962,1987]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1690,1713]" captionTargetBox="[165,1417,193,1648]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1424,193,1669]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Arboridia cincta Song &amp; Li, sp. nov.: 1, Abdominal apodemes; 2, Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 3, Subgenital plate; 4, Style; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238916/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="586">Figs 5, 6</figureCitation>
). Connective V-shaped, lateral arms long and stem short (
<figureCitation box="[1225,1293,1962,1987]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1690,1713]" captionTargetBox="[165,1417,193,1648]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1424,193,1669]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Arboridia cincta Song &amp; Li, sp. nov.: 1, Abdominal apodemes; 2, Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 3, Subgenital plate; 4, Style; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238916/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="586">
Fig. 
<number box="[1277,1293,1963,1987]" pageId="2" pageNumber="586" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1782,2023]" box="[199,1123,1998,2023]" pageId="2" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,370,1998,2023]" pageId="2" pageNumber="586">Measurement.</emphasis>
Body length males 
<quantity box="[594,731,1999,2023]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="3.3" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="586" unit="mm" value="3.25" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="3.2">3.2–3.3 mm</quantity>
, females 
<number box="[837,920,1999,2023]" pageId="2" pageNumber="586" value="3.3499999999999996" valueMax="3.4" valueMin="3.3">3.3–3.4</number>
(including wing).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,445,151,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587">Specimen examined.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[453,562,151,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587">Holotype</typeStatus>
: ♂, 
<collectingCountry box="[610,702,152,176]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="587">CHINA</collectingCountry>
, Henan Prov., Mt. Baiyun, 
<date box="[1014,1167,152,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587" value="2008-08-17">
<number box="[1014,1040,152,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587" value="17.0">17</number>
-VIII- 
<number box="[1108,1167,152,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</date>
, coll. Yuehua Song and Can Li (
<collectionCode box="[243,329,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587">GUGC</collectionCode>
). 
<typeStatus box="[347,460,189,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587">Paratypes</typeStatus>
: 
<number box="[470,484,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587" value="9.0">9</number>
♂♂, 
<number box="[541,575,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587" value="10.0">10</number>
♀♀ (
<collectionCode box="[625,710,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587">GUGC</collectionCode>
), 
<number box="[729,742,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587" value="3.0">3</number>
♂♂, 
<number box="[800,818,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587" value="2.0">2</number>
♀♀ (
<collectionCode box="[870,953,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587">GZNU</collectionCode>
), same data as 
<typeStatus box="[1122,1224,188,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587">holotype</typeStatus>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,223,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Sohi &amp; Mann (1992)" authorityName="Sohi &amp; Mann" authorityYear="1992" box="[613,980,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Arboridia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dziubka">
<emphasis box="[613,630,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="587">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[645,732,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="587">dziubka</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sohi" box="[740,980,223,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587" refString="Sohi, A. S. &amp; Mann, J. S. (1992) Fourteen new species and some new records of Asian Erythroneurini (Insecta, Auchenorrhyncha, Cicadellidae: Typhlocybinae). Reichenbachia, 29 (22), 123 - 143." type="journal article" year="1992">
Sohi &amp; 
<collectingCountry box="[830,895,224,247]" name="Isle of Man" pageId="3" pageNumber="587">Mann</collectingCountry>
(
<number box="[912,972,224,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587" value="1992.0">1992</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in having the aedeagus with just one pair of apical processes, arising from the two sides of the gonopore (
<figureCitation box="[1043,1148,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1690,1713]" captionTargetBox="[165,1417,193,1648]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1424,193,1669]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Arboridia cincta Song &amp; Li, sp. nov.: 1, Abdominal apodemes; 2, Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 3, Subgenital plate; 4, Style; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238916/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="587">Figs 5, 6</figureCitation>
); the aedeagus preatrium much longer than the dorsal apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[584,650,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1690,1713]" captionTargetBox="[165,1417,193,1648]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1424,193,1669]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Arboridia cincta Song &amp; Li, sp. nov.: 1, Abdominal apodemes; 2, Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 3, Subgenital plate; 4, Style; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238916/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="587">
Fig. 
<number box="[636,650,295,320]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) and the pygofer dorsal appendage with many microspines at the apex (
<figureCitation box="[159,229,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1690,1713]" captionTargetBox="[165,1417,193,1648]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[162,1424,193,1669]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Arboridia cincta Song &amp; Li, sp. nov.: 1, Abdominal apodemes; 2, Pygofer lobe, lateral view; 3, Subgenital plate; 4, Style; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238916/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="587">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,229,332,356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="587" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
